import React from 'react'
import {View,Text} from 'react-native'

export default function ComputerScreen() {
    const Data=[
        {}
    ]
  return (
    <View style={{flex:1,backgroundColor:'#f2f2f0'}}>
            <View style={{width:'100%',height:'15%',backgroundColor:'#2f7a8f',
            alignItems:'center',justifyContent:'center',marginBottom:20}}>
        <Text style={{fontSize:32,fontWeight:'bold',color:'white'}}>All Type MCQs</Text>
    </View>
    <View style={{flex:1,marginVertical:10,alignItems:'center'}}>
        <View style={{width:'90%',height:'35%',borderRadius:20,backgroundColor:'white',elevation:4}}>
            <Text style={{margin:10,fontSize:16,color:'green',fontWeight:'bold'}}>The term ‘Computer’ is derived from__________?</Text>
             
             <View style={{marginLeft:20}}>
            <Text style={{margin:4,fontSize:18,fontWeight:'bold'}}>A. Latin</Text>
             <Text style={{margin:4,fontSize:18,}}>B. German</Text>
             <Text style={{margin:4,fontSize:18,}}>C. French</Text>
             <Text style={{margin:4,fontSize:18,}}>D. Arabic</Text>
             </View>
        </View>
    </View>

    </View>
  )
}
